
1. What is the main purpose of using Named Range in Google Sheets?

	Named Ranges assign human-readable names to cells/ranges, replacing complex references like A1:A100 with simple names like SalesData.

Purpose:

    Simplify formulas (=SUM(SalesData) vs =SUM(A1:A100))

    Reduce errors when copying formulas

    Team collaboration - others understand instantly

    Dynamic updates - change range once, affects all formulas



2. How do Named Ranges make formulas easier?

Before Named Range:

text
=SUM(A2:A100)+AVERAGE(A2:A100)*COUNT(A2:A100)
# Tedious to type, error-prone, hard to read

After Named Range "MonthlySales":

text
=SUM(MonthlySales)+AVERAGE(MonthlySales)*COUNT(MonthlySales)
# Clean, fast autocomplete, obvious meaning

Benefits:

    Autocomplete - type "Mon" → picks MonthlySales

    Copy-paste safe - no broken references

    Readable - like variables in programming

    Dynamic - expand range once, everywhere updates



3. What rules must be followed for naming a range?

| ✅ ALLOWED     | ❌ NOT ALLOWED                   |
| ------------- | ------------------------------- |
| Sales2026     | 2Sales (no numbers first)       |
| Total_Amount  | Total Amount (no spaces)        |
| Q1_Revenue    | Total-Sales (no hyphens)        |
| IndiaSales    | sales data (no lowercase start) |
| Max 250 chars | Special chars except _          |

Best Practices:

✅ Descriptive: Sales_Jan2026
✅ Short: Q1, Budget
✅ Consistent: snake_case or CamelCase



4. Can you edit or delete a Named Range? How?

Access Named Ranges:

    Data → Named ranges (sidebar opens)

    See all names with their ranges

Edit:

Click name → Change range → Done
"Sales" was A1:A10 → Now A1:A20
All formulas using "Sales" update automatically!

Delete:

Click name → Remove → All formulas still work (convert to cell refs)



5. When should you prefer Named Range over normal cell reference?

| Scenario            | Example                        |
| ------------------- | ------------------------------ |
| Repeated references | Same range in 3+ formulas      |
| Team sheets         | Others need to understand      |
| Long/complex ranges | Sheet1!A2:B1000 → Database     |
| Dynamic data        | Monthly sales that grows       |
| Dashboards          | KPI ranges like Revenue, Costs |

Skip for:

    One-off calculations

    Disposable analysis

    Simple 1-cell refs

Pro Example:

Named: "Employees", "Salaries", "Departments"
Dashboard: =SUM(Salaries)/COUNTA(Employees)
Add new employee → Update "Employees" range once → Done!

Named Ranges = Professional spreadsheets! 🚀